Rating: 4
This pie was AMAZING. The crust was tasty and flaky and the apples were the perfect consistency. It was perfect. I did modify it slightly though: I used granny smith apples, which did not result in soup. My only question that I wasn't able to roll the pate brisee thin enough for the bottom crust to properly meet the top crust with a 1-inch overhang; I therefore wasn't able to squeeze quite all the apples in. And as for baking it, I did end up putting it back in the oven on about 325 for 15 minutes after the recommended baking time (after it had cooled), because the bottom was still undercooked. I put aluminum foil on the top and this seemed to work fine. This is a great, basic, tasty and delicious apple pie!

