Rating: 0
Recently looked through a book containing nothing but apple pie recipes. Sure enough, I learned that Granny Smiths release more water during the cooking process than most any variety of apple. Whereas McIntosh's become softer and absorb more liquid than most any other baking apple. Hence the apple soup. The book suggested increasing flour whenever using Granny Smiths only or vice versa when it came to McIntosh's in other recipes. Just need to play with the proportions a little... I think a mix of the two apples with a little more flour should be just right.

