Rating: 0
Note to Brenda Daily (if you happen to look back through these reviews): If you had looked through the reviews before making this pie, you would have seen that, a) many people recommended doubling the crust, which is consistant with most double-crust recipes I've seen, and, b) most people who raved about the recipe listed the varieties of apples they used, which were NOT MacIntosh. Macs are known for turning to mush and I have never before seen them recommended in a pie recipe. And thicker crusts would have held together better when rolling. I strongly suggest you read through reviews before making recipes; that's one of the great things about this site. Recipes printed in books and magazines are not always thoroughly tested, so it makes sense to take advantage of all the home testers that are willing to take the time and submit their feedback online.

